Tourism Minister, Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane, will host a virtual media briefing on Tourism related activities under Risk-Adjusted level 3, update on Tourism Relief Fund and Relief fund for Tourist Guides. JOHANNESBURG - Tourism Minister Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane will hold a virtual media briefing on Thursday. Kubayi-Ngubane will give an update on activities in the tourism sector under Risk-Adjusted Level 3. She will also outline provide details on the tourism relief fund and the relief fund for tourist guides. READ: Tourism sector urged to use winter season to gear up The industry has been hard hit with holiday and leisure facilities being shut down during the lockdown. This has resulted in millions of rands being lost in revenue. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131,